(15, '', 'Samsung once again posts all-time high revenue in Q4 2021 driven by strong sales of foldables, S ser', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-346814&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Samsung-Galaxy-Z-Fold-3-5G_FoneArena-9-1024x640.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;359&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Samsung has reported its earnings for Q4 2021 that ended December 31, 2021 in which the company posted 76.57 trillion won ($63.6 billion approx.) consolidated revenue, up 24.4% YoY which is the new high beating the previous record. This is due to finished product businesses, with expanded sales of premium smartphones, including foldable phones, as well as TVs and home appliances.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355687&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;more-351242&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It made an operating profit of 13.87 trillion won ($11.5 billion approx.), up 53.25% YoY due to profits in semiconductor businesses, but it declined QoQ due to special bonus payment to employees, said Samsung.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For the full year, it reported 279.6 trillion won in revenue, a new historic high, up 18% compared to 2020 and 51.63 trillion in operating profit, up 43.45 YoY.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Samsung Mobile in Q4 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;IM sector that includes Mobile Communications and Networks Businesses posted 28.95 trillion won consolidated revenue, up 29.5% YoY and 2.66 trillion won operating profit for the quarter, up 9.91%. Increase in profits is due to increase in premium smartphones including foldable lineup and Galaxy S series.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Samsung said that device Ecosystem products such as PCs, tablets and wearables have also contributed to the revenue growth. Meanwhile, increased marketing expenses to boost foldable category sales and prepare for the launch of new models in Q1 2022 had impact on profitability to some degree.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Display Business&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Display Panel Business saw earnings continue to improve for mobile panels, while losses in large panels widened due to price declines in LCDs and costs related to QD displays.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The mobile panel business saw its earnings continue to improve, primarily driven by solid demand for newly launched smartphones from its key customers. In addition, increased sales of products for new applications including laptops and gaming consoles contributed to the mobile panel earnings.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In 2022, solid demand for OLED is likely to continue despite macro environment-related risks, based on the rising penetration of 5G and growth of the foldable market. Samsung will pursue a balanced business structure for stable growth by expanding Flexible OLED to mid-range devices as well as diversifying applications for Rigid OLED including IT, gaming and automotive.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Q1 2022 expectations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;For the first quarter, demand for smartphones and tablets is expected to decline QoQ amid weak seasonality as well as uncertainties over component supply. However, the MX Business aims to secure solid profitability by expanding flagship sales such as Galaxy S21 FE and upcoming release of a new Galaxy S22 series. Samsung is expected to introduce a new competitive mass-market 5G smartphone lineup to drive sales.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Samsung says that it is expecting uncertainties related to prolonged pandemic and component shortage will persist in 2022. Yet, the smartphone market is expected to continue to grow, and the wearable market is likely to see a double-digit growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The MX Business will solidify its leadership in the flagship market by accelerating innovations and differentiated experiences such as Galaxy S and foldable series, while strengthening the competitiveness of mass-market 5G lineup and Device Ecosystem products.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In 2022, the Memory Business expects server demand to grow, attributed to increase in IT investments and new high-core CPUs, while 5G lineup expansion is likely to increase content-per-box for mobile, although challenges related to supply issues and COVID-19 are likely to persist.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355687&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- /1044778/300x250 --&gt;&lt;div id=\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\' style=\'height:250px; width:300px;margin-left:30px;\'&gt;&lt;script type=\'text/javascript\'&gt;\ngoogletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display(\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\'); });\n&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-info&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-avatar&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-avatar --&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;author-title&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;author-heading&quot;&gt;Author:&lt;/span&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;author-bio&quot;&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar is a Mobile Technology Enthusiast who is passionate about Mobile phones and Mobile apps. He uses the phones he reviews as his main phone. You can follow him on  &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://instagram.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;author-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/author/srivatsan&quot; rel=&quot;author&quot;&gt; View all posts by Srivatsan Sridhar			&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!-- .author-bio --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-description --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-info --&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Samsung-Galaxy-Z-Fold-3-5G_FoneArena-9-', '', 'Samsung-once-again-posts-all-time-high-revenue-in-Q4-2021-driven-by-strong-sales-of-foldables-S-series-phones', 'draft', 'Samsung once again posts all-time high revenue in Q4 2021 driven by strong sales of foldables, S series phones', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:12:16'),
(16, '', 'Xiaomi, Redmi and POCO MIUI 13 Update Tracker [Update: MIUI 13 Global Released for Redmi Note 10 Jap', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-353584&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/MIUI-13-logo.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;402&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi announced the current iteration of its proprietary Android skin – MIUI on December 28. To those unaware, MIUI versions are independent of the Android versions that means the devices (Xiaomi, Redmi, and POCO)  that aren’t eligible to get Android 12 update might at least get MIUI 13 update. This post will help our readers in keeping a track of MIUI 13 related news, rollout schedule, and rollout status.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;more-352333&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Xiaomi, Mi, Redmi, and POCO Devices that have received MIUI 13 Global Update&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/335995/redmi-note-10-miui-12-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Note 10&lt;/a&gt; (Global, Pilot Release)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/335146/redmi-note-10-pro-redmi-note-10-pro-max-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro&lt;/a&gt; (Global, Pilot Release)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Lite (Global, Pilot Release)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10 Japan Edition (Global, Stable)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h5 class=&quot;entry-title&quot;&gt;Also take a look at &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/351752/xiaomi-android-12-update-tracker-redmi-poco.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Xiaomi, Redmi and POCO Android 12 Update Tracker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Jan 27, 2022]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Redmi Note 10 Japan Edition MIUI 13 Stable update, based on &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/351752/xiaomi-android-12-update-tracker-redmi-poco.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Android 12&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, has been released. The update comes with firmware version MIUI 13.0.2.0.SKRJPKD. The handset is known as Redmi Note 10T 5G in India and Redmi Note 10 5G Globally.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Jan 23, 2022]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 Lite&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13 Global Stable update, based on &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/351752/xiaomi-android-12-update-tracker-redmi-poco.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Android 12&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, has been released for Pilot testers. The update comes with firmware version MIUI 13.0.2.0.SKQ&lt;strong&gt;MI&lt;/strong&gt;XM.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Jan 22, 2022]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 10&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13 Global Stable update, based on &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/351752/xiaomi-android-12-update-tracker-redmi-poco.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Android 12&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, has been released for Pilot testers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/335995/redmi-note-10-miui-12-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Note 10&lt;/a&gt;– MIUI 13.0.3.0.SKG&lt;strong&gt;MI&lt;/strong&gt;XM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/335146/redmi-note-10-pro-redmi-note-10-pro-max-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro&lt;/a&gt; – MIUI 13.0.2.0.SKF&lt;strong&gt;MI&lt;/strong&gt;XM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Jan 18, 2022]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomiui &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/xiaomiui/status/1483380997261570052&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;claims&lt;/a&gt; that Xiaomi has implemented Material You UI (Monet theming engine) in MIUI 13 with the latest MIUI 13 China Beta build 22.1.17.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Jan 18, 2022]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomiui has &lt;a href=&quot;https://xiaomiui.net/miui-13-is-coming-to-poco-x3-pro-and-poco-f3-very-soon-3646/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;spotted&lt;/a&gt; references to &lt;strong&gt;Android 12 based MIUI 13 Global&lt;/strong&gt; Stable builds for POCO F3 and POCO X3 Pro. The respective firmware versions are,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POCO F3 &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.1.0.SKHEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POCO F3 &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.1.0.SKHMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POCO X3 Pro &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.1.0.SJUMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Jan 15, 2022]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomiui has &lt;a href=&quot;https://xiaomiui.net/miui-13-update-is-coming-soon-for-mi-11x-and-mi-11-lite-5g-ne-3274/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;spotted&lt;/a&gt; references to &lt;strong&gt;Android 12 based MIUI 13 India&lt;/strong&gt; Stable builds for Xiaomi 11 Lite NE 5G and Xiaomi Mi 11X. The respective firmware versions are,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11X&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.1.0.SKHINXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Xiaomi 11 Lite NE 5G &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.1.0.SKHINXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Dec 28, 2o21]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi MIUI 13 has been &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/354254/miui-13-supported-devices-features.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;announced&lt;/a&gt; in China. To learn about the MIUI 13 China features and first look, you can head over to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/354402/miui-13-features-first-look-mi-11x-pro.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;this post&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Dec 21, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi has &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/353869/xiaomi-12-launch-date.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;confirmed&lt;/a&gt; that the MIUI 13 will be introduced on &lt;strong&gt;December 28th&lt;/strong&gt; in China.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Dec 20, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomiui has &lt;a href=&quot;https://xiaomiui.net/miui-13-global-first-builds-and-first-batch-devices-list-have-been-announced-1652/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;spotted&lt;/a&gt; references to &lt;strong&gt;Android 12 based MIUI 13 Global Stable&lt;/strong&gt; builds for several devices in MIUI source code. These devices along with the firmware versions are,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;MIUI 13 India (IN) Builds&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11X &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.0.1.SKHINXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11X Pro&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.3.SKKINXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 10T Pro &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.0.1.SJDINXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 10 T&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SJDINXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POCO F3 GT&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SKJINXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POCO X3 Pro&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.2.SJUINXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h5&gt;MIUI 13 European (EU) Builds&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 Ultra&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.3.SKAEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.0.1.SKBEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11i&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.3.SKKEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Xiaomi 11T Pro &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.0.4.SKDEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Xiaomi 11T&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SKWEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POCO F3&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SKHEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 Lite 5G &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.0.5.SKIEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 Lite 4G&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SKQEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 10T Pro&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SJDEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 10T&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SJDEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.0.4.SKFEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 10 &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.0.1.SKGEUXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h5&gt;MIUI 13 Global (MI) Builds&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 Ultra&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.5.SKAMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.7.SKBMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11i&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.5.SKKMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Xiaomi 11T Pro&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.3.SKDMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Xiaomi 11T &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.0.1.SKWMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 Lite 5G&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.5.SKIMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 Lite 4G&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.9.SKQMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 10&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SJBMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 10T Pro&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SJDMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 10T&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SJDMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POCO F3&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SKHMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POCO F2 Pro&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SJKMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POCO X3 Pro &lt;/strong&gt;MIUI 13.0.0.3.SJUMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POCO X3 GT&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.1.SKPMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.6.SKFMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 10&lt;/strong&gt; MIUI 13.0.0.2.SKGMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Dec 14, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div id=\'gallery-1\' class=\'gallery galleryid-352333 gallery-columns-2 gallery-size-large\'&gt;&lt;figure class=\'gallery-item\'&gt;&lt;div class=\'gallery-icon portrait\'&gt;&lt;a href=\'https://www.fonearena.com/blog/352333/xiaomi-miui-13-update-tracker-redmi-poco.html/miui-13-setup-fonearena-2\'&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;468&quot; height=&quot;1024&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/MIUI-13-Setup-FoneArena-2-468x1024.png&quot; class=&quot;attachment-large size-large&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure class=\'gallery-item\'&gt;&lt;div class=\'gallery-icon portrait\'&gt;&lt;a href=\'https://www.fonearena.com/blog/352333/xiaomi-miui-13-update-tracker-redmi-poco.html/miui-13-setup-fonearena-1\'&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;468&quot; height=&quot;1024&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/MIUI-13-Setup-FoneArena-1-468x1024.png&quot; class=&quot;attachment-large size-large&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;MIUI 13 logo and welcome screen screenshots have now surfaced. &lt;a href=&quot;https://xiaomiui.net/miui-13-logo-is-official-with-screenshots-and-setup-screen-1240/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Xiaomiui&lt;/a&gt; obtained these screenshots from the MIUI Feedback app and the Setup screen app.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[Dec 9, 2021]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi will suspend the MIUI China Beta update for all the devices starting 13th December. Xiaomi, in a post on the Chinese forum, said,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Due to the adjustment of the software system architecture, the MIUI development version will be suspended for a period of time starting from 12.13, always believe that beautiful things are about to happen&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[Dec 2, 2021]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;A new &lt;a href=&quot;https://xiaomiui.net/miui-13-build-of-poco-x3-gt-and-poco-f3-gt-are-getting-ready-854/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;finding&lt;/a&gt; by Xiaomiui suggests that MIUI 13 China Stable build (based on Android 12) for Redmi K40 Gaming Edition (known as POCO F3 GT in India) and Redmi Note 10 Pro 5G (known as POCO X3 GT globally) have entered into the testing phase.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi K40 Gaming Edition: V13.0.0.1.SKJCNXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro 5G: V13.0.0.1.SKPCNXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;These devices might get MIUI 13 China Stable update on the day of MIUI 13 announcement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[Nov 22, 2021]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;A new report by &lt;a href=&quot;https://xiaomiui.net/miui-beta-brings-new-miui-health-app-395/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Xiaomiui&lt;/a&gt; suggests that MIUI 13 (China) will bring with it a newly redesigned Health app with Xiaomi Wear integration. The new Health app adds two new sections – &lt;strong&gt;Devices &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;My Account&lt;/strong&gt;. The Devices section will let users manage their Xiaomi wearable within the Mi Health app itself. Apart from it, the existing &lt;strong&gt;Health Dashboard &lt;/strong&gt;and&lt;strong&gt; Workouts &lt;/strong&gt;sections will also get a visual overhaul.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone size-large&quot; src=&quot;https://pbs.twimg.com/media/FEkrd6NXEAINZkD?format=jpg&amp;amp;name=large&quot; width=&quot;2048&quot; height=&quot;2048&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[Nov 21, 2021]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomiui, a Xiaomi-focused blog, has &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/xiaomiui/status/1462064274390532098&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;shared&lt;/a&gt; a new list of devices eligible to get MIUI 13. We would like to emphasize that this list is not shared by Xiaomi, so there might be changes in the official list.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://pbs.twimg.com/media/FEpLrHYWYAYzxQ6?format=jpg&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[Nov 18, 2021]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;A new &lt;a href=&quot;https://xiaomiui.net/miui-13-stable-is-almost-ready-ready-for-xiaomi-flagships-325/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;finding&lt;/a&gt; by Xiaomiui suggests that MIUI 13 China Stable build (based on Android 12) for several devices have entered into the testing phase. These devices and their respective firmware versions are as follows,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi Mix 4: V13.0.0.1.SKMCNXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Ultra: V13.0.0.1.SKACNXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Pro: V13.0.0.1.SKACNXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11: V13.0.0.1.SKBCNXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Lite 5G: V13.0.0.1.SKICNXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 10S: V13.0.0.1.SGACNXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi K40 Pro+: V13.0.0.1.SKKCNXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi K40 Pro: V13.0.0.1.SKKCNXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi K40: V13.0.0.1.SKHCNXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;We can expect some of these devices to get MIUI 13 Stable update on the day of MIUI 13 announcement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[Nov 16, 2021]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi has announced a list of devices that will not receive MIUI 12.5 Enhanced update. So, the chances for these devices to receive MIUI 13 are also slim now, the list includes,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/280625/poco-f1-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;POCO F1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/280214/xiaomi-redmi-note-7-pro-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Note 7 Pro&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/279737/redmi-note-7-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Note 7S&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/279737/redmi-note-7-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Note 7&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/282950/redmi-7-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi 7&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/286616/xiaomi-redmi-y3-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Y3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi 7A&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi A3&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[Nov 4, 2021]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi co-founder, Lei Jun, confirms that MIUI 13 will be unveiled (in China) by the end of the year.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_352333&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/MIUI-13-logo.jpg', '', 'Xiaomi-Redmi-and-POCO-MIUI-13-Update-Tracker-Update-MIUI-13-Global-Released-for-Redmi-Note-10-Japan-Edition-', 'draft', 'Xiaomi, Redmi and POCO MIUI 13 Update Tracker [Update: MIUI 13 Global Released for Redmi Note 10 Japan Edition]', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:12:40'),
(17, '', 'MediaTek Kompanio 1380 6nm SoC for ultra-light premium Chromebooks, tablets announced', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355684&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/MediaTek-Kompanio.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;425&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Acer at the CES earlier this month introduced its new Chromebook Spin 513 powered by an Octa-Core MediaTek Kompanio 1380 processor. Now, MediaTek has officially announced the company’s flagship Kompanio SoC which uses TSMC’s 6nm process tech. This has four high-performance Cortex-A78 cores clocked up to 3GHz and four Cortex-A55 power-efficiency-focused cores. There is a five-core Arm Mali-G57 GPU.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355682&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt; There is 4K60 HDR Display Support, AV1 Hardware Decoding, has a dedicated audio digital signal processor (DSP) that provides ultra-low power voice on wakeup (VoW) capabilities and comes with Wi-Fi 6/6E and Bluetooth 5 connectivity.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355683&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Chromebook-Spin-513-2022.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;573&quot; height=&quot;418&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MediaTek Kompanio 1380 (MT8195T) specifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Octa-Core – 4x Arm Cortex-A78 up to 3GHz, 4x Arm Cortex-A55 up to 2GHz&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Arm Mali-G57 MC5 GPU&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;TSMC 6nm process&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2133MHz LPDDR4X memory, eMMC / uFS / NVMe storage&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;MediaTek APU 3.0 with 4 TOPS performance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;16 MP + 16MP camera, 3840 x 2160 (4K) video recording&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;2520 x 1080 (Full HD+), 2560 x 1600 (2.5K) and 3840 x 2160 (4K) display resolution support&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Supports up to three independent displays total; two 4K60 HDR displays or 2.5K up to 120Hz&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;H.264, H.265 / HEVC encode, H.264, H.265 / HEVC, VP-9 and AV1 decode, 7.1 surround sound audio&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Wi-Fi 6 / 6E (a/b/g/n/ac/ax), Bluetooth 5.0, GNSS: GPS, Glonass, BeiDou, Galileo, QZSS&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;The MediaTek Kompanio 1380 will roll out in coming months, and the new Acer Chromebook Spin 513 powered by the chip will roll out from April starting at US$ 599.99 (Rs. 45,065 approx.).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355682&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- /1044778/300x250 --&gt;&lt;div id=\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\' style=\'height:250px; width:300px;margin-left:30px;\'&gt;&lt;script type=\'text/javascript\'&gt;\ngoogletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display(\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\'); });\n&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-info&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-avatar&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-avatar --&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;author-title&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;author-heading&quot;&gt;Author:&lt;/span&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;author-bio&quot;&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar is a Mobile Technology Enthusiast who is passionate about Mobile phones and Mobile apps. He uses the phones he reviews as his main phone. You can follow him on  &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://instagram.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;author-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/author/srivatsan&quot; rel=&quot;author&quot;&gt; View all posts by Srivatsan Sridhar			&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!-- .author-bio --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-description --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-info --&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/MediaTek-Kompanio.jpg', '', 'MediaTek-Kompanio-1380-6nm-SoC-for-ultra-light-premium-Chromebooks-tablets-announced', 'draft', 'MediaTek Kompanio 1380 6nm SoC for ultra-light premium Chromebooks, tablets announced', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:12:40'),
(18, '', 'MIUI 13 global roll out begins Q1 2022 – Check out list of Xiaomi devices getting it', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355674&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/MIUI-13-logo-1024x721.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;404&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;After the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/354254/miui-13-supported-devices-features.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;announcement&lt;/a&gt; in China last month, Xiaomi along with the Redmi Note 11 series introduced the MIUI 13 for the global markets. This doesn’t bring several features that were launched in China, but only finetunes some features that were already available with the &lt;a title=&quot;MIUI 12.5 Enhanced to bring further system optimizations &amp;mdash; Global roll out details and list of devices getting it&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/347292/miui-12-5-enhanced-supported-devices-roll-out-date-global.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;MIUI 12.5 Enhanced&lt;/a&gt;. These include Faster storage, Faster background efficiency, Faster processing and Longer battery life.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355673&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355675&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/MIUI-13-features-1024x504.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;282&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Liquid Storage on MIUI 13 reduces fragmentation and actively manages stored data, improving defragmentation efficiency by up to 60%. MIUI 13 retains read and write speeds up to 95%—giving users a “new” experience longer, and prolonging device lifespan.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;MIUI 13’s Atomized Memory, an ultra-fine memory management method, brings RAM efficiency to a new level. It analyzes how apps use memory and divides a single app’s RAM usage processes into important and unimportant tasks. Then it closes all unimportant tasks, allowing apps to use memory only for what’s important to you right now, enabling you to run more apps without sacrificing performance.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;MIUI 13 brings Focused Algorithms, which dynamically allocates system resources based on usage scenarios, making MIUI more fluid and responsive. Focused Algorithms prioritizes the active app above all others, allowing the CPU to focus on important tasks, giving you faster speeds and higher performance where and when you need it.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Smart Balance in MIUI 13 is designed to automatically find the balance between performance and power consumption, so you can get the power and speed you need to stay on the go. With Smart Balance, overall battery life can be extended by up to 10% in MIUI 13.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;With all-new widgets, you can personalize the smartphones with convenient modules and notifications in the App Vault or on the home screen. MIUI 13 supports widgets of different sizes. With 2×1, 2×2, 2×3, 4×2, and 4×4 options at hand, users can fit more important information on a single widget and place widgets where they may not have fit before.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355676&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/MIUI-13-Sidebar-1024x576.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;323&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sidebar in MIUI 13 allows you to access all your favorite apps in floating windows with just a swipe—without leaving your current app. You can also customize the feature with up to 10 apps in the sidebar.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First batch of models that will get the MIUI 13 update globally in Q1 2022&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Ultra&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11i&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Lite 5G&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Lite&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Xiaomi 11T Pro&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Xiaomi 11T&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Xiaomi 11 Lite 5G NE&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Xiaomi 11 Lite NE&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 11 Pro 5G&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 11 Pro&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 11S&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 11&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro Max&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10 JE&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 8 (2021)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi 10&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Xiaomi Pad 5&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi 10 Prime&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11X&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11X Pro&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;We can expect India-specific roll out details at the Redmi Note 11S launch in the country on February 9th.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355673&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- /1044778/300x250 --&gt;&lt;div id=\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\' style=\'height:250px; width:300px;margin-left:30px;\'&gt;&lt;script type=\'text/javascript\'&gt;\ngoogletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display(\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\'); });\n&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-info&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-avatar&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-avatar --&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;author-title&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;author-heading&quot;&gt;Author:&lt;/span&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;author-bio&quot;&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar is a Mobile Technology Enthusiast who is passionate about Mobile phones and Mobile apps. He uses the phones he reviews as his main phone. You can follow him on  &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://instagram.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;author-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/author/srivatsan&quot; rel=&quot;author&quot;&gt; View all posts by Srivatsan Sridhar			&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!-- .author-bio --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-description --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-info --&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/MIUI-13-logo-1024x721.jpg', '', 'MIUI-13-global-roll-out-begins-Q1-2022-Check-out-list-of-Xiaomi-devices-getting-it', 'draft', 'MIUI 13 global roll out begins Q1 2022 – Check out list of Xiaomi devices getting it', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:12:40'),
(19, '', 'Redmi Note 11 with 6.43? FHD+ 90Hz AMOLED display, Snapdragon 680, 50MP quad rear cameras, 5000mAh b', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone size-large wp-image-355663&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Redmi-Note-11-1-1024x927.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;840&quot; height=&quot;760&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Along with the Note 11S, Redmi also introduced the Redmi Note 11, the company’s latest budget smartphone in the Redmi Note 11 series for the global markets. It has a 6.43-inch Full HD+ AMOLED screen with 90Hz refresh rate, 16MP selfie camera inside the punch-hole, is powered by Snapdragon 680 SoC, and packs a 50MP main camera, 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP depth and a 2MP macro camera.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355661&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;more-355657&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355666&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Redmi-Note-11-features-1024x512.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;287&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It has a side-mounted fingerprint scanner and packs a 5000mAh battery with 33W fast charging that can charge up to 100% in around an hour.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 11 specifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;6.43-inch FHD+ (1080×2400 pixels) AMOLED display with 90Hz refresh rate, DCI-P3 color gamut, 1000 nits peak brightness&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Octa Core Snapdragon 680 6nm Mobile Platform with Adreno 610 GPU&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;4GB LPDDR4X RAM with 64GB / 128GB UFS 2.2 internal storage, 6GB LPDDR4X RAM with 128GB UFS 2.2 internal storage, expandable memory up to 1TB with microSD&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Android 11 with MIUI 13&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Dual SIM (nano + nano + microSD)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;50MP rear primary camera with f/1.8 aperture, 8MP 118° ultra-wide angle camera, 2MP depth and 2MP macro camera with f/2.4 aperture&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;13MP front camera with f/2.4 aperture&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Side-mounted fingerprint sensor, IR blaster&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;3.5mm audio jack, Stereo speakers, Hi-Res Audio certification&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Dimensions:159.87 x 73.87 x 8.09mm; Weight: 179g&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Splash resistant (IP53)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Dual 4G VoLTE, Wi-Fi 802.11 ac (2.4GHz + 5GHz), Bluetooth 5.0, GPS + GLONASS, USB Type-C, NFC (select markets only)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;5000mAh (typical) battery with 33W fast charging&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Redmi Note 11 comes in Star Blue, Twilight Blue and Graphite Gray colours and is priced at $179 (Rs. 13,405 approx.) for 4GB+64GB, $199 (Rs. 14,905 approx.) for 4GB+128GB and $229 (Rs. 17,150 approx. for 6GB + 128GB models. Early bird pricing will start at $159 when it goes on sale on January 28th and 29th on AliExpress.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&quot;twitter-tweet&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;???????????? ????????:????????,&lt;br/&gt; We know you have been wishing for more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Exceeding your expectations was never a trouble,&lt;br/&gt; We are here to &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hashtag/SetTheBar?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;&gt;#SetTheBar&lt;/a&gt; and make it ????????????????????????!???? &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/4OMg5VCvAr&quot;&gt;pic.twitter.com/4OMg5VCvAr&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;— Redmi India – Redmi Note 11S (@RedmiIndia) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/RedmiIndia/status/1486574938823618561?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;&gt;January 27, 2022&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;script async src=&quot;https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Update: Xiaomi has started teasing the launch of Redmi Note 11 along with the Note 11S in India on February 9th.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355661&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- /1044778/300x250 --&gt;&lt;div id=\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\' style=\'height:250px; width:300px;margin-left:30px;\'&gt;&lt;script type=\'text/javascript\'&gt;\ngoogletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display(\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\'); });\n&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-info&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-avatar&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-avatar --&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;author-title&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;author-heading&quot;&gt;Author:&lt;/span&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;author-bio&quot;&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar is a Mobile Technology Enthusiast who is passionate about Mobile phones and Mobile apps. He uses the phones he reviews as his main phone. You can follow him on  &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://instagram.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;author-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/author/srivatsan&quot; rel=&quot;author&quot;&gt; View all posts by Srivatsan Sridhar			&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!-- .author-bio --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-description --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-info --&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Redmi-Note-11-1-1024x927.jpg', '', 'Redmi-Note-11-with-6-43-FHD-90Hz-AMOLED-display-Snapdragon-680-50MP-quad-rear-cameras-5000mAh-battery-announced', 'draft', 'Redmi Note 11 with 6.43? FHD+ 90Hz AMOLED display, Snapdragon 680, 50MP quad rear cameras, 5000mAh battery announced', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:12:40'),
(20, '', 'Redmi Note 11S with 6.43? FHD+ 90Hz AMOLED display, Helio G96, 108MP quad rear cameras, 5000mAh batt', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355658&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Redmi-Note-11S.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;412&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;After &lt;a title=&quot;Redmi Note 11S with 108MP camera launching in India on February 9&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/355027/redmi-note-11s-india-launch-date.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;confirming&lt;/a&gt; the India launch on February 9th, Redmi has introduced the Redmi Note 11S smartphone for the global markets. It has a 6.43-inch Full HD+ AMOLED screen with 90Hz refresh rate, 16MP selfie camera inside the punch-hole, is powered by Helio G96 SoC, and packs a 108MP main camera, 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP depth and a 2MP macro camera.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355657&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355659&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Redmi-Note-11S-features-1024x512.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;287&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It has a side-mounted fingerprint scanner and packs a 5000mAh battery with 33W fast charging that can charge up to 100% in around an hour.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 11S specifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;6.43-inch FHD+ (1080×2400 pixels) AMOLED display with 90Hz refresh rate, DCI-P3 color gamut, 1000 nits peak brightness&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Octa Core MediaTek Helio G96 12nm processor (Dual 2.05GHz A76 + Hexa 2GHz A55 CPUs) with Mali-G57 MC2 GPU&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;6GB LPDDR4X RAM with 64GB UFS 2.2 internal storage, 6GB / 8GB LPDDR4X RAM with 128GB UFS 2.2 internal storage, expandable memory up to 1TB with microSD&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Android 11 with MIUI 13&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Dual SIM (nano + nano + microSD)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;108MP rear primary camera with Samsung HM2 sensor, f/1.9 aperture, 8MP 118° ultra-wide angle camera, 2MP depth and 2MP macro camera with f/2.4 aperture&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;16MP front camera with f/2.4 aperture&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Side-mounted fingerprint sensor, IR blaster&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;3.5mm audio jack, Stereo speakers, Hi-Res Audio certification&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Dimensions:159.87 x 73.87 x 8.09mm; Weight: 179g&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Splash resistant (IP53)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Dual 4G VoLTE, Wi-Fi 802.11 ac (2.4GHz + 5GHz), Bluetooth 5.0, GPS + GLONASS, USB Type-C, NFC (select markets only)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;5000mAh (typical) battery with 33W fast charging&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Redmi Note 11S comes in Pearl White, Twilight Blue and Graphite Gray colours, is priced at $249 (Rs. 18,650 approx.) for 6GB+64GB, $279 (Rs. 20,895 approx.) for 6GB+128GB and $299 (Rs. 22,395 approx. for 8GB + 128GB models. Early bird pricing will start at $229 when it goes on sale on January 28th and 29th on AliExpress.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We should know the price of the phone in India when it is launched next month. The phone is also expected to launch in some markets as POCO M4 Pro 4G with a slight change in design.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355657&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- /1044778/300x250 --&gt;&lt;div id=\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\' style=\'height:250px; width:300px;margin-left:30px;\'&gt;&lt;script type=\'text/javascript\'&gt;\ngoogletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display(\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\'); });\n&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-info&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-avatar&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-avatar --&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;author-title&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;author-heading&quot;&gt;Author:&lt;/span&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;author-bio&quot;&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar is a Mobile Technology Enthusiast who is passionate about Mobile phones and Mobile apps. He uses the phones he reviews as his main phone. You can follow him on  &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://instagram.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;author-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/author/srivatsan&quot; rel=&quot;author&quot;&gt; View all posts by Srivatsan Sridhar			&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!-- .author-bio --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-description --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-info --&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Redmi-Note-11S.jpg', '', 'Redmi-Note-11S-with-6-43-FHD-90Hz-AMOLED-display-Helio-G96-108MP-quad-rear-cameras-5000mAh-battery-announced', 'draft', 'Redmi Note 11S with 6.43? FHD+ 90Hz AMOLED display, Helio G96, 108MP quad rear cameras, 5000mAh battery announced', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:12:40');
