(41, '', 'Sony launches two wireless neckband speakers in India', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355506&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Sony-SRS-NS7.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;573&quot; height=&quot;460&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sony, on Monday launched two new wireless neckband speakers – SRS-NB10 and SRS-NS7 in India.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355500&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;SRS-NB10&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Sony-SRS-NB10.jpg&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;First off, the SRS-NB10 is designed for online conferences and meetings during work from home. The neckband features a full-range speaker angled upward and passive radiators for a well-balanced sound.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The SRS-NB10 comes with Voice Pickup Technology for clear calls, two high-quality directional microphones combined with advanced audio signal processing for noise minimisation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As per the company’s claims, the wireless neckband is light and comfortable with a secure fit. The company also promises 20 hours of battery life, and 10 minutes quick charge gives up to an hour of extra work or play. It features a USB Type-C port and comes with IPX4 splash-proof certification.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/SRS-NS7.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;371&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;SRS-NS7&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;On the other hand, the SRS-NS7 is the world’s first Dolby Atmos compatible wireless neckband speaker with Sony’s BRAVIA XR models. It delivers Sony’s unique 360 Spatial Sound experience with the 360 Spatial Sound Personalizer app.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;To use it to its full potential, one needs to connect the supplied wireless transmitter WLA-NS7 to the TV with an optical cable and USB cable, then pair the SRS-NS7 with the transmitter via Bluetooth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;To customise the experience, users can install the 360 Spatial Sound Personalizer smartphone app. As of Oct 2021, the compatible devices are as follows – WF-1000XM3, WH-1000XM4, WH-XB700, WI-1000XM2.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The SRS-NS7 features an X-Balanced Speaker unit, an upward-facing speaker, and a passive radiator for an immersive music experience.  As per the company’s claims, the SRS-NS7 provides up to 12 hours of power and up to 5 hours at maximum volume.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It also supports quick charging with USD type-C, and a 10-minutes of charge gives you up to an extra 60 minutes of extra playtime. Like the SRS-NB10, it also has an IPX4 splash-proof design.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The new SRS-NB10, SRS-NS7 wireless neckband speakers, and WLA-NS7 wireless transmitter will be available across all Sony Center, E-commerce portals from today.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pricing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;SRS-NB10 – Rs. 11,990&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;SRS-NS7 – Rs. 22,990&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;WLA-NS7 – Rs. 5,690&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355500&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Sony-SRS-NS7.jpg', '', 'Sony-launches-two-wireless-neckband-speakers-in-India', 'draft', 'Sony launches two wireless neckband speakers in India', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:13:04'),
(42, '', 'Samsung Galaxy S22 series pricing surface ahead of announcement on February 9', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355425&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Samsung-Galaxy-Unpacked-2022-1024x573.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;575&quot; height=&quot;322&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Last week, Samsung &lt;a title=&quot;Samsung confirms Galaxy Unpacked event for February; says it will release a Noteworthy S series&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/355424/samsung-galaxy-unpacked-2022-galaxy-s22-teaser.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;confirmed&lt;/a&gt; its Galaxy Unpacked event in February. Now, the pricing for the entire Galaxy S22 series have surfaced in Europe. This reveals that the Galaxy S22 will start at €849 and €1049 starting price for the S22+, same as the S21 and S21+ released last year, but the €1,249 price tag for the S22 Ultra 8GB + 128GB is more since the company launched the 12GB + 128GB S21 Ultra model for the same price last year.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355498&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The company might launch the 16GB + 512GB version is select markets, since it is missing in this list. This also doesn’t mention the rumoured 16GB + 1TB option that might also be limited to some markets.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Samsung-Galaxy-S22-Ultra-render.jpg&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;392&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Samsung Galaxy S22 series rumoured Europe pricing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Samsung Galaxy S22 8GB + 128GB  – €849 (US$ 961 / Rs. 71,720 approx.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Samsung Galaxy S22 8GB + 256GB – €899 (US$ 1,020 / Rs. 75,955 approx.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Samsung Galaxy S22+ 8GB + 128GB –  €1049 (US$ 1188 / Rs. 88,630 approx.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Samsung Galaxy S22+ 8GB + 256GB  €1099 (US$ 1,245 / Rs. 92,815 approx.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Samsung Galaxy S22 Ultra 8GB + 128GB – €1,249 (US$ 1414 / Rs. 1,05,485 approx.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Samsung Galaxy S22 Ultra 12GB + 256GB –  €1,349 (US$ 1,527 / Rs. 1,13,930 approx.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Samsung Galaxy S21 Ultra 5G 12GB + 512GB – €1,449 (US$ 1641 / Rs. 1,22,415 approx.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Samsung Galaxy Unpacked virtual event is scheduled for February 9, 2022 at 10 AM EST (8:30 PM IST) and will be streamed live.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We should know all the details when the Galaxy S22 series go official in a couple of weeks. The Galaxy Tab S8 series should also be introduced at the same event.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/rquandt/status/1484689280425414661&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355498&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- /1044778/300x250 --&gt;&lt;div id=\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\' style=\'height:250px; width:300px;margin-left:30px;\'&gt;&lt;script type=\'text/javascript\'&gt;\ngoogletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display(\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\'); });\n&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-info&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-avatar&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-avatar --&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;author-title&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;author-heading&quot;&gt;Author:&lt;/span&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;author-bio&quot;&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar is a Mobile Technology Enthusiast who is passionate about Mobile phones and Mobile apps. He uses the phones he reviews as his main phone. You can follow him on  &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://instagram.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;author-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/author/srivatsan&quot; rel=&quot;author&quot;&gt; View all posts by Srivatsan Sridhar			&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!-- .author-bio --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-description --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-info --&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Samsung-Galaxy-Unpacked-2022-1024x573.j', '', 'Samsung-Galaxy-S22-series-pricing-surface-ahead-of-announcement-on-February-9', 'draft', 'Samsung Galaxy S22 series pricing surface ahead of announcement on February 9', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:13:04'),
(43, '', 'Apple reportedly planning to launch ‘widest array of new hardware products in its history’ this fall', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355496&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Apple-device-lineup-1024x501.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;573&quot; height=&quot;281&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We have already heard &lt;a title=&quot;Apple iPhone SE 3 with 4.7-inch display, 5G support expected in March or April&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/354827/apple-iphone-se-3-launch-rumour.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;reports&lt;/a&gt; that Apple will hold an event in March or April to introduce iPhone SE 5G and a &lt;a title=&quot;Apple said to launch new iPad Air with A15 chip, Center Stage camera and 5G support&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/355135/apple-ipad-air-5-2022-rumor.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;new iPad Air&lt;/a&gt; with A15 chip. According to Mark Gurman on Bloomberg’s Power On newsletter, Apple will not launch a new iPad Pro in the Spring, but a new model with an updated design, M2 chip and wireless charging later.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355484&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;He said that M1 Pro chip will power a new Mac in the first half of this year, which could be the long &lt;a title=&quot;Apple Mac Mini with M1X processor and more ports expected in the coming months&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/346909/apple-mac-mini-m1x-processor-rumour.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;rumoured&lt;/a&gt; higher-end Mac mini or iMac. However, the new MacBook Air and Mac Pro models are expected only later this year.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fall event 2022&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;“Apple is readying the widest array of new hardware products in its history this fall,” says Gurman. Here’s what to expect:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;iPhone 14 Pro could feature a pill-shaped camera cutout; iPhone SE 4 with iPhone 11-like design, punch-hole screen expected in 2024&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/354775/iphone-14-pro-pill-shaped-camera-iphone-se-4-2024-rumor.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;iPhone 14, 14 mini&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;a title=&quot;Apple iPhone 14 Pro and iPhone 14 Pro Max said to feature 6.1-inch &amp;zwnj;and 6.7-inch &amp;zwnj;LTPO OLED 120Hz punch-hole display&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/353347/iphone-14-pro-iphone-14-pro-max-display-specs-rumor.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt; 14 Pro and 14 Pro Max&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Low-end MacBook Pro&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Updated iMac&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New Mac Pro&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Apple said to release new MacBook Air with white bezels, new colours in 2022&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/351013/apple-macbook-air-2022-white-bezels-new-colours-rumour.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Revamped MacBook Air&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Apple AirPods Pro 2nd gen could feature Apple Lossless support, sound-emitting charging case&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/354520/apple-airpods-pro-2-apple-lossless-charging-case-rumor.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;AirPods Pro upgrade&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Apple said to launch updated Watch SE and rugged variant for sports athletes in 2022&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/353169/apple-watch-se-rugged-2022-rumor.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Three Apple Watch models&lt;/a&gt; – Series 8, SE, and Rugged&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New low-end iPad&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;2nd Gen AirPods Pro and new iPad Pro with updated design may arrive in 2022&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/348807/airpods-pro-2-ipad-pro-6th-gen-2022-rumor.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;New iPad Pro&lt;/a&gt; with M2 chip, wireless charging&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;For the WWDC in June which will also likely be a virtual event, it should introduce iOS 16 (Sydney), tvOS 16 (Paris), macOS 13 (Rome), and watchOS 9 (Kincaid), but no hardware devices are expected.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2022-01-23/when-will-apple-aapl-release-new-iphone-se-5g-and-ipad-air-apple-spring-event-kyrmlang&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355484&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- /1044778/300x250 --&gt;&lt;div id=\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\' style=\'height:250px; width:300px;margin-left:30px;\'&gt;&lt;script type=\'text/javascript\'&gt;\ngoogletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display(\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\'); });\n&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-info&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-avatar&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-avatar --&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;author-title&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;author-heading&quot;&gt;Author:&lt;/span&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;author-bio&quot;&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar is a Mobile Technology Enthusiast who is passionate about Mobile phones and Mobile apps. He uses the phones he reviews as his main phone. You can follow him on  &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://instagram.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;author-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/author/srivatsan&quot; rel=&quot;author&quot;&gt; View all posts by Srivatsan Sridhar			&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!-- .author-bio --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-description --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-info --&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Apple-device-lineup-1024x501.jpg', '', 'Apple-reportedly-planning-to-launch-widest-array-of-new-hardware-products-in-its-history-this-fall', 'draft', 'Apple reportedly planning to launch ‘widest array of new hardware products in its history’ this fall', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:13:04'),
(44, '', 'Google reportedly working on a new Chromecast powered by Google TV', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Google-Chromecast-Apple-TV-app.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;327&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It seems Google is working on a new device similar to Chromecast with Google TV. In 2020, Google &lt;a title=&quot;Google introduces new Chromecast with Google TV, 4K HDR support, voice remote for $49.99&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/323947/google-chromecast-2020-price-features.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;launched&lt;/a&gt; a Chromecast with Google TV support, but many criticised it for the lack of storage.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355491&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As per the latest report, Google is working on an Android-powered device under the codename ‘Boreal’. The report adds that Boreal was found in the same family as Sabrina, which is the current Chromecast with Google TV.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;“The Boreal is directly connected to the same Google TV Chromecast software for Android that powers the Chromecast with Google TV,” says the report.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;However, there is not much information about the device now, however, it is expected to contain hardware decoding support for the AV1 format, a spec that was missing from the Chromecast with Google TV.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;On the other hand, Google is reportedly &lt;a title=&quot;Google reportedly working on AR headset &amp;ldquo;Project Iris&amp;rdquo; to take on Apple and Meta&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/355442/googl-ar-headset-project-iris-take-on-apple-meta.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;working&lt;/a&gt; on its pair of AR headsets in a project internally codenamed as Project Iris to compete against the likes of Apple and Meta. Google is said to be planning to ship the device by 2024.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://9to5google.com/2022/01/21/google-tv-chromecast-2022/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355491&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Google-Chromecast-Apple-TV-app.jpg', '', 'Google-reportedly-working-on-a-new-Chromecast-powered-by-Google-TV', 'draft', 'Google reportedly working on a new Chromecast powered by Google TV', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:13:04'),
(45, '', 'OPPO Reno7 and Reno7 Pro launching in India on February 4', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355486&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/OPPO-Reno-7-Series-India-launch-teaser-1024x537.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;573&quot; height=&quot;301&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Update: January 24, 2022 – OPPO has confirmed the launch of Reno7 series – Reno7 Pro 5G and Reno7 5G in India on February 4, 2022. These will feature a proprietary OPPO Glow design that incorporates aircraft-grade Laser Direct Imaging (LDI) technology, said the company.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355321&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;OPPO Glow is a design technology where the glass back cover of the phone achieves two seemingly paradoxical properties: Matte texture and a shiny appearance. These make the phones fingerprint and stain-resistant. The newer LDI technology has been repurposed to etch fine textures—as small as 20 microns in size—onto the photoresist-coated AG glass back cover of the Reno7 series, said OPPO.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It added that each device’s back features a total of 1.2 million micro-etchings that create the illusion of thousands of stars—complete with long tails of light—shining across the sky. These micron-scale etchings give the phones a matte in-hand feel and brushed finish.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355487&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/OPPO-Reno-7-Pro-teaser.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;396&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Reno7 Pro feature a lightweight, yet durable aluminum middle frame offering a flat-edge design making it easier to hold and operate. The smartphone feature a 6.55-inch FHD+ 2.5D OLED screen, which the company says it the narrowest bezel packaging process in the history Reno. This makes the left and right black edges of the screen 0.2mm narrower. The Reno7 Pro is 11.5% thinner than last gen’s Reno with a 92.8% ultra-large screen-to-body ratio and weighs 180 grams.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-352586&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/OPPO-Reno-7-Pro-light.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;572&quot; height=&quot;270&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Reno7 Pro also uses first-of-its-kind 3D “breathing” lights around the camera module. Here, a 1mm diameter fibre is bent to frame the camera area and emit soft, pulsating lights whenever the phone receives a call, message, or during charging.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;OPPO Reno7 Pro 5G and Reno7 5G will come in Startails Blue and Starlight Black colours.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355374&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/OPPO-Reno-7-India-launch-teaser-1024x599.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;336&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Earlier: OPPO &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/352573/oppo-reno-7-price-specifications-reno-7-pro-reno-7-se.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;introduced&lt;/a&gt; the OPPO 7 series in China in November last year, now the company has started teasing the smartphones in India ahead of launch. The company is calling the Reno7 Pro 5G portrait expert, since it will feature  Sony’s new 32MP IMX709 selfie sensor. It will also feature a 50MP IMX766 rear camera sensor.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355375&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/OPPO-Reno-7-Pro-camera-teaser-1024x584.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;327&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The IMX709—exclusive to OPPO—is a customised RGBW (red, blue, green, white) front image sensor that can capture crisper and more evenly-exposed photos and videos; it is 60% more sensitive to light and reduces noise by 30% when compared to traditional RGB sensors.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For selfies, the Reno7’s front camera automatically switches from 85° to a 90° angle when it detects more than two people in the viewfinder to capture multi-person snapshots. Additionally, in portrait photos, camera algorithms separate the subject in the foreground, detect light sources in the background to produce a soft lens flare and finally, blur the background for a more natural-looking Bokeh flare effect.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Reno7 Pro 5G has a IMX766 large rear sensor that captures more light when shooting photos and videos. It also supports 26 adjustable bokeh levels, said OPPO. It also has Bokeh Flare Portrait video that accurately identifies the human subject in any complex background that we had seen in the Reno 6 series.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Both, the IMX709 and IMX766, support DOL-HDR technology which increases the dynamic range to shoot well-exposed images and detailed low-light videos; the cameras capture multiple long-exposure and short-exposure frames almost simultaneously and fuse them into a single vibrant snapshot.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Since it is running a lucky draw from 20th Jan. to 4th Feb, we can expect the launch in the first week of February.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355321&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- /1044778/300x250 --&gt;&lt;div id=\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\' style=\'height:250px; width:300px;margin-left:30px;\'&gt;&lt;script type=\'text/javascript\'&gt;\ngoogletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display(\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\'); });\n&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-info&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-avatar&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-avatar --&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;author-title&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;author-heading&quot;&gt;Author:&lt;/span&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;author-bio&quot;&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar is a Mobile Technology Enthusiast who is passionate about Mobile phones and Mobile apps. He uses the phones he reviews as his main phone. You can follow him on  &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://instagram.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;author-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/author/srivatsan&quot; rel=&quot;author&quot;&gt; View all posts by Srivatsan Sridhar			&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!-- .author-bio --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-description --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-info --&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/OPPO-Reno-7-Series-India-launch-teaser-', '', 'OPPO-Reno7-and-Reno7-Pro-launching-in-India-on-February-4', 'draft', 'OPPO Reno7 and Reno7 Pro launching in India on February 4', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:13:04'),
(46, '', 'OnePlus 10R with Dimensity 9000, 120Hz AMOLED display said to launch in Q2 2022', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355117&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/OnePlus-9RT-Nano-Silver-and-Hacker-Black-1024x818.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;458&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;OnePlus &lt;a title=&quot;OnePlus 10 Pro with 6.7&amp;Prime; QHD+ 120Hz AMOLED display, Snapdragon 8 Gen 1, up to 12GB RAM, 5000mAh battery, 80W fast charging announced&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/354928/oneplus-10-pro-price-specifications.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;introduced&lt;/a&gt; its flagship 10 Pro this month in China, and the OnePlus 9RT was launched in India a couple of weeks back, months after it was introduced in China. Now, the company is reportedly planning to launch the OnePlus 10R as the successor of 9R or 9RT in the coming months.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355482&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;According to the report from &lt;em&gt;Android Central, &lt;/em&gt;the OnePlus 10R will be powered by MediaTek’s flagship &lt;a title=&quot;MediaTek Dimensity 9000 4nm SoC to power Redmi K50 series, OPPO Find X series, HONOR and vivo phones in Q1 2022&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/353702/mediatek-dimensity-9000-devices-redmi-k50-oppo-find-x-honor-vivo.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Dimensity 9000&lt;/a&gt;. OPPO, vivo, Xiaomi and HONOR already confirmed that they will launch their flagship smartphones powered by the chip in the first quarter of 2022, but the OnePlus was not in the list.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We still don’t have the camera specs of the phone, and it is not clear if it will include Hasselblad camera features. It is said to come with 120Hz AMOLED screen, same as the 9RT.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The OnePlus 10R is expected to be introduced by the end of Q2 2022, which is sometime in May or June in India and China.  The OnePlus 10, successor to the OnePlus 9 and global launch of the OnePlus 10 Pro are expected in early Q2, which is sometime in April.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.androidcentral.com/oneplus-10r-mediatek-dimensity-9000-exclusive&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355482&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- /1044778/300x250 --&gt;&lt;div id=\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\' style=\'height:250px; width:300px;margin-left:30px;\'&gt;&lt;script type=\'text/javascript\'&gt;\ngoogletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display(\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\'); });\n&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-info&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-avatar&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-avatar --&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;author-title&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;author-heading&quot;&gt;Author:&lt;/span&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;author-bio&quot;&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar is a Mobile Technology Enthusiast who is passionate about Mobile phones and Mobile apps. He uses the phones he reviews as his main phone. You can follow him on  &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://instagram.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;author-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/author/srivatsan&quot; rel=&quot;author&quot;&gt; View all posts by Srivatsan Sridhar			&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!-- .author-bio --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-description --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-info --&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/OnePlus-9RT-Nano-Silver-and-Hacker-Blac', '', 'OnePlus-10R-with-Dimensity-9000-120Hz-AMOLED-display-said-to-launch-in-Q2-2022', 'draft', 'OnePlus 10R with Dimensity 9000, 120Hz AMOLED display said to launch in Q2 2022', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:13:30'),
(47, '', 'Micromax IN Note 2 with 6.43? AMOLED display, Helio G95 launching on January 25', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355478&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Micromax-IN-Note-2-1024x824.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;462&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Micromax has announced the launch of IN Note 2, the company’s upcoming smartphone in the IN Note series and the successor to IN Note 1 that was launched back in November 2020. The company has posted a teaser that confirms a 6.43? AMOLED screen with a centre punch-hole camera, minimal bezels on the top and a glass finish on the back.&lt;span id=&quot;more-355477&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;alignnone wp-image-355480&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Micromax-In-Note-2-launch-date.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;574&quot; height=&quot;270&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The image also shows a 48MP rear camera along with three other cameras which should be ultra-wide, depth and macro cameras. Micromax has also confirmed that it will be powered by a MediaTek Helio G95 SoC, so it will be a 4G phone. It will come with support for 30W fast charging that can charge the phone up to 50% in 25 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The phone will feature a side-mounted fingerprint sensor. A Micromax smartphone with the model number E7446 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/344697/micromax-in-2-benchmark-leak.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;surfaced&lt;/a&gt; in benchmarks last year, revealing MediaTek Helio G95 SoC clocked at 2GHz and paired with 4GB RAM and Android 11.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Micromax In Note 2 will come in Brown and Black colours, and will be sold on Flipkart. We should know the price of the phone when it is launched tomorrow, January 25th.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_355477&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- /1044778/300x250 --&gt;&lt;div id=\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\' style=\'height:250px; width:300px;margin-left:30px;\'&gt;&lt;script type=\'text/javascript\'&gt;\ngoogletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display(\'div-gpt-ad-1466626458146-0\'); });\n&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-info&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-avatar&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-avatar --&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;author-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;author-title&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;author-heading&quot;&gt;Author:&lt;/span&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;author-bio&quot;&gt; Srivatsan Sridhar is a Mobile Technology Enthusiast who is passionate about Mobile phones and Mobile apps. He uses the phones he reviews as his main phone. You can follow him on  &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://instagram.com/ssrivatsan&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;author-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/author/srivatsan&quot; rel=&quot;author&quot;&gt; View all posts by Srivatsan Sridhar			&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!-- .author-bio --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-description --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .author-info --&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Micromax-IN-Note-2-1024x824.jpg', '', 'Micromax-IN-Note-2-with-6-43-AMOLED-display-Helio-G95-launching-on-January-25', 'draft', 'Micromax IN Note 2 with 6.43? AMOLED display, Helio G95 launching on January 25', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:13:30'),
(48, '', 'Xiaomi, Redmi and POCO Android 12 Update Tracker [Update: Android 12 Released for Redmi Note 10, Red', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&quot;lazy&quot; class=&quot;aligncenter size-full wp-image-351774&quot; src=&quot;https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Xiaomi-Mi-Redmi-POCO-Android-12-FoneArena-e1636473271429.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Xiaomi Redmi POCO Android 12&quot; width=&quot;776&quot; height=&quot;351&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Google introduced the latest version of its mobile operating system – Android 12 back in October. Similar to every other Android OEM, Xiaomi will roll out Android 12 for a host of devices. However, the brand hasn’t announced the list of smartphones eligible to receive the Android 12 update. This post will help our readers in keeping a track of Android 12 Update for Xiaomi, Mi, Redmi, and POCO devices.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;more-351752&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Xiaomi, Mi, Redmi, and POCO Devices that have received Android 12 based MIUI Update:&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Ultra (Global, Pilot Release)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 (Global, Pilot Release)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/340696/mi-11x-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Mi 11i&lt;/a&gt; (Global, Pilot Release)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Pro (China Stable)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/340696/mi-11x-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi K40 Pro+&lt;/a&gt; (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi K40 Pro (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/340696/mi-11x-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi K40&lt;/a&gt; (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 10S (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Lite 5G (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 10 Ultra (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 10 Pro (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/313392/xiaomi-mi-10-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Mi 10&lt;/a&gt; (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Xiaomi Civi (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/344886/poco-f3-gt-miui-software-update-tracker-update-miui-12-5-4-0-with-july-android-security-patch.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi K40 Gaming Edition&lt;/a&gt; (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro 5G (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 11 Pro 5G (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 11 Pro+ 5G (China Beta)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/335995/redmi-note-10-miui-12-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Note 10&lt;/a&gt; (Global, Pilot Release)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/335146/redmi-note-10-pro-redmi-note-10-pro-max-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro&lt;/a&gt; (Global, Pilot Release)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Lite (Global, Pilot Release)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h5 class=&quot;entry-title&quot;&gt;Also take a look at &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/352333/xiaomi-miui-13-update-tracker-redmi-poco.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Xiaomi, Redmi and POCO MIUI 13 Update Tracker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Jan 23, 2022]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 Lite&lt;/strong&gt; Android 12 Stable update has been released for Pilot testers. The update comes with firmware version MIUI 13.0.2.0.SKQ&lt;strong&gt;MI&lt;/strong&gt;XM.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Jan 22, 2022]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 10&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro&lt;/strong&gt; Android 12 Stable update has been released for Pilot testers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/335995/redmi-note-10-miui-12-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Note 10&lt;/a&gt;– MIUI 13.0.3.0.SKG&lt;strong&gt;MI&lt;/strong&gt;XM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/335146/redmi-note-10-pro-redmi-note-10-pro-max-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro&lt;/a&gt; – MIUI 13.0.2.0.SKF&lt;strong&gt;MI&lt;/strong&gt;XM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Jan 21, 2022]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi, with MIUI China Beta 22.1.19 update, brings Android 12 to &lt;b&gt;Redmi Note 11 Pro &lt;/b&gt;(known as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/355292/xiaomi-11i-xiaomi-11i-hypercharge-miui-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Xiaomi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;strong&gt;11i&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in India&lt;strong&gt;) &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;b&gt;Redmi Note 11 Pro+ &lt;/b&gt;(known as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/355292/xiaomi-11i-xiaomi-11i-hypercharge-miui-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Xiaomi &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;11i HyperCharge&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in India)&lt;b&gt;.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Jan 4, 2022]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi has suspended MIUI China Beta update for &lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 11 5G &lt;/strong&gt;(known as &lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 11T 5G&lt;/strong&gt; in India and &lt;strong&gt;POCO M4 Pro 5G &lt;/strong&gt;globally) ahead of Android 12 update.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Dec 8, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi has suspended MIUI China Beta update for &lt;strong&gt;Mi 10 Youth&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;strong&gt; Redmi K30 5G&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;strong&gt; Redmi K30i 5G&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;strong&gt; Redmi Note 9 Pro 5G&lt;/strong&gt; (known as &lt;strong&gt;Mi 10i&lt;/strong&gt; in India), &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/355292/xiaomi-11i-xiaomi-11i-hypercharge-miui-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 11 Pro&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (known as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/355292/xiaomi-11i-xiaomi-11i-hypercharge-miui-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Xiaomi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;strong&gt;11i&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in India), and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/355292/xiaomi-11i-xiaomi-11i-hypercharge-miui-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 11 Pro+&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (known as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/355292/xiaomi-11i-xiaomi-11i-hypercharge-miui-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Xiaomi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;strong&gt;11i&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; HyperCharge in India) ahead of Android 12 update.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Dec 2, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi, with MIUI China Beta 21.11.30 update, brings Android 12 to &lt;strong&gt;Mi 10 Pro&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Mi 10&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Redmi K30 Pro&lt;/strong&gt; (known as &lt;strong&gt;POCO F2 Pro&lt;/strong&gt; Globally), and &lt;strong&gt;Redmi K30S Ultra&lt;/strong&gt; (known as &lt;strong&gt;Mi 10T&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Nov 30, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi has suspended MIUI China Beta update for &lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 10 5G &lt;/strong&gt;(known as &lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 10T 5G&lt;/strong&gt; in India and &lt;strong&gt;POCO M3 Pro 5G &lt;/strong&gt;globally) ahead of Android 12 update.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Nov 16, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi, with MIUI China Beta 21.11.15 update, brings Android 12 to &lt;strong&gt;Mi 10 Ultra&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Xiaomi Civi&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Nov 10, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi has once again started &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/349530/mi-11-ultra-mi-11-mi-11i-android-12-stable-testing-program.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;recruiting &lt;/a&gt;testers for MIUI Global Stable ROM, based on Android 12, for &lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 Ultra&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Mi 11&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/340696/mi-11x-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11i&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (known as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/340696/mi-11x-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11X Pro&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in India and &lt;strong&gt;Redmi K40 Pro+&lt;/strong&gt; in China). It said that it will recruit only 200 members for each device.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Nov 9, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi, with MIUI China Beta 21.11.8 update, brings Android 12 to &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/344886/poco-f3-gt-miui-software-update-tracker-update-miui-12-5-4-0-with-july-android-security-patch.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi K40 Gaming Edition&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; (known as &lt;strong&gt;POCO F3 GT&lt;/strong&gt; in India) and &lt;strong&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro 5G&lt;/strong&gt; (known as &lt;strong&gt;POCO X3 GT&lt;/strong&gt; Globally).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Nov 8, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi suspends MIUI China Beta update for several devices ahead of Android 12 update. We can expect these devices to get Android 12 update in the next couple of weeks, the list includes,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Xiaomi Civi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 10 Ultra&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 10 Pro&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/313392/xiaomi-mi-10-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Mi 10&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi K30 Pro&lt;/strong&gt; (known as &lt;strong&gt;POCO F2 Pro&lt;/strong&gt; Globally)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi K30S Ultra&lt;/strong&gt; (known as &lt;strong&gt;Mi 10T&lt;/strong&gt; Globally)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Nov 3, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&quot;twitter-tweet&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;List of devices that will receive Android 12&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Internal Android 12 testing of Redmi Note 10 JE (iris), Redmi Note 11 Pro / Pro+(pissarro), Xiaomi 11T (agate), Xiaomi 11 Lite NE (lisa), Xiaomi CIVI (mona), Redmi Note 10S (rosemary) are started.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This list updated on 2 November 2021 &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/yf7upOV8KU&quot;&gt;pic.twitter.com/yf7upOV8KU&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;— Xiaomiui | Xiaomi &amp; MIUI News (@xiaomiui) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/xiaomiui/status/1455620045787353090?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;&gt;November 2, 2021&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi has &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/351599/xiaomi-android-12-internal-testing.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;reportedly&lt;/a&gt; begun Android 12 based MIUI China Beta ROM testing for a host of devices including&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Xiaomi 11 Lite NE&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Xiaomi 11T Pro&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Xiaomi 11T&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Xiaomi Civi&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Lite 4G&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Lite 5G&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 10 Lite 5G&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 11&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 11 Pro&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 11 Pro+&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10S&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10 Pro Max&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 10 5G (known as Redmi Note 10T in India)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 9 Pro 5G (known as Mi 10i in India and Mi 10T Lite Globally)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi Note 8 (2021)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi 10&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi K30 5G&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Redmi K30i 5G&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;POCO X3 Pro&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;POCO M3 Pro 5G&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Oct 21, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi, with MIUI China Beta 21.10.20 update, brings Android 12 to &lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 Lite 5G&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Oct 16, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi, with MIUI China Beta 21.10.13 update, brings Android 12 to &lt;strong&gt;Mi 10S&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/340696/mi-11x-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redmi K40&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (known as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/340696/mi-11x-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11X&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in India and &lt;strong&gt;POCO F3&lt;/strong&gt; Globally).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Oct 6, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi is rolling out Android 12 based MIUI Global Stable Beta update for Pilot testers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 Ultra – MIUI 12.5.3.0.SKAMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11 – MIUI 12.5.3.0.SKBMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mi 11i – MIUI 12.5.4.0.SKKMIXM&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Oct 2, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi, with MIUI China Beta 21.9.29 update, brings Android 12 to Mi 11 Ultra, and Mi 11 Pro.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Sep 30, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/349530/mi-11-ultra-mi-11-mi-11i-android-12-stable-testing-program.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;announces&lt;/a&gt; MIUI Global Stable ROM Testing program, based on Android 12, for &lt;strong&gt;Mi 11 Ultra&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Mi 11&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/340696/mi-11x-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11i&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;(known as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/340696/mi-11x-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mi 11X Pro&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in India and Redmi K40 Pro+ in China).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;[Sep 24, 2021]&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Xiaomi, with MIUI China Beta 21.9.22 update, brings Android 12 to Mi 11, Redmi K40 Pro, and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fonearena.com/blog/340696/mi-11x-miui-software-update-tracker.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Redmi K40 Pro+&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; (known as Mi 11X Pro in India and Mi 11i Globally).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note: We will keep updating this list as Xiaomi starts testing or releases Android 12 update for more smartphones.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cs-rating pd-rating&quot; id=&quot;pd_rating_holder_1304431_post_351752&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;', 'https://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Xiaomi-Mi-Redmi-POCO-Android-12-FoneAre', '', 'Xiaomi-Redmi-and-POCO-Android-12-Update-Tracker-Update-Android-12-Released-for-Redmi-Note-10-Redmi-Note-10-Pro-and-Mi-11-Lite-Pilot-Testers-', 'draft', 'Xiaomi, Redmi and POCO Android 12 Update Tracker [Update: Android 12 Released for Redmi Note 10, Redmi Note 10 Pro, and Mi 11 Lite Pilot Testers]', 1, 28, '2022-01-29 08:13:30');
