(2, 'Micromax IN Note 1', 'micromax-phones', 15499, 0, '/Public/assets/images/default.jpg', '&amp;lt;span&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Micromax In 1 is the newly launched smartphone that is available at a starting price of Rs 10,499. The phone features a metallic finish with an X pattern on the back and decent specifications. This lightweight and sleek smartphone weighs approximately 195 grams and its dimensions are 165.4 mm x 76.8 mm x 8.9 mm (height x width x thickness).&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt;  &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;This dual SIM smartphone from Micromax accepts both Nano-SIM and Nano-SIM cards. The phone features a 6.67 inches capacitive touchscreen display that has a resolution of 1080x2400 pixels with 91.4 percent screen-to-body ratio and 400 nits peak brightness that gives you an immersive experience at the time of watching videos or playing games. Moreover, Micromax In 1 runs the Android 10 operating system that offers you a user-friendly and clutter-free user interface. And, the phone is housed with a 5000mAh non-removable battery that supports proprietary fast charging. Hence, you need not worry about battery drainage in the middle of a task, playing a game, watching a video, clicking pictures and doing various other things.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Speaking about the optics, Micromax In 1 comes with a triple camera setup on the rear that lets you click some superb pictures and record high quality videos. The phone features a 48 MP primary camera with f/1.79 aperture, a 2 MP macro camera with f/2.4 aperture, and a 2 MP depth sensor with f/2.4 aperture. Camera features on the rear setup include touch to focus, auto flash, face detection, digital zoom, and more. Apart from this, you can click some awesome selfies and make video calls as this new smartphone from Micromax comes with an 8 MP front camera.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Micromax In 1 offers you a smooth and lag-free performance while playing games with intense graphics, browsing the web, and accessing multiple apps as it is equipped with Octa core (2 GHz, Dual core, Cortex A75 + 1.8 GHz, Hexa Core, Cortex A55) MediaTek Helio G80 processor. In addition to this, the smartphone comes with a RAM capacity of 4GB and 64GB of inbuilt storage that can be expanded up to 256GB using a microSD card using a dedicated slot. Owing to such amazing RAM and storage capacity, you can conveniently store all your pictures, videos, games, songs and other files without any space restrictions.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;There are various connectivity options that come on the Micromax In 1 smartphone such as 4G (with support for Band 40 used by some LTE networks in India), 3G, 2G, Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, GPS, Bluetooth v5.00, USB Type-C, and 3.5mm audio jack. Sensors on the phone include a rear fingerprint sensor, accelerometer, gyroscope, proximity sensor, and ambient light sensor. Also, the mobile supports face unlock.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;You can buy the Micromax In 1 in Blue and Purple color options.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h6&amp;gt;Micromax IN Note 1 Price In India&amp;lt;/h6&amp;gt;Micromax IN Note 1 smartphone price in India is Rs 10,950. Micromax IN Note 1 was launched in the country on November 3, 2020 (Official). Thesmartphone comes in 1 other storage and RAM variants - Micromax-IN-Note-1-128GB-4GB-RAM. As for the colour options, the Micromax IN Note 1 smartphone comes in White, Green colours.&amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;', '', '{\"keyspecs\":{\"0\":\"\",\"ram\":\"4 GB\",\"processor\":\"MediaTek Helio G85 (MT6769V\\/CZ)\",\"rear camera\":\"48 MP + 5 MP + 2 MP + 2 MP\",\"front camera\":\"16 MP\",\"battery\":\"5000 mAh\",\"display\":\"6.67 inches\"},\"general\":{\"0\":\"\",\"launch date\":\"November 3, 2020 (Official)\",\"price in india\":\"10999\",\"brand\":\"Micromax\",\"model\":\"IN Note 1\",\"operating system\":\"Android v10 (Q)\",\