(604, 'Xiaomi Redmi Note 9 Pro Max', 'xiaomi-phones', 16999, 0, 'https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/resizemode-4,msid-74564440,imgsize-400,width-270/74564440.jpg', '&amp;lt;div id=&amp;quot;&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;lIZA8&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;height:auto&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;span&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Redmi Note 9 Pro Max is a popular smartphone by Xiaomi that is highly appreciated for its outstanding performance. Loaded with advanced features and decent specifications, Redmi Note 9 Pro Max is available at a starting price of Rs 14,999 in Aurora Blue, Glacier White, Interstellar Black, and Champagne Gold color options. This sleek and lightweight mobile weighs around 209 grams and measures 165.50 mm x 76.68 mm x 8.80 mm (height x width x thickness). &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Redmi Note 9 Pro Max Camera&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;: Speaking about the optics of Redmi Note 9 Pro Max, it comes with a quad-camera setup that lets you click amazing pictures. It has a 64 MP primary camera with f/1.9 aperture, an 8 MP image sensor with f/2.2 aperture, a 5 MP sensor with f/2.4 aperture, and a 2 MP depth sensor with f/2.4 aperture. Features on the rear camera setup include AI beautify, tilt-shift custom watermark, pro mode, portrait mode, panorama mode, and more. On the front, you get a 32 MP camera for selfies and video chats. &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Redmi Note 9 Pro Max Display, OS and Battery&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;: You can have a crystal clear and immersive viewing experience while watching movies and playing games as the Redmi Note 9 Pro Max features a 6.67 inches FHD+ resolution DotDisplay that has a resolution of 1080x2400 pixels. With the Corning Gorilla Glass 5 protection, your display is protected from scratches and breakage. &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;The smartphone from Xiaomi runs Android 10 OS with MIUI 11 and is powered by a 5,020mAh non-removable battery with support for 33W fast charging. Furthermore, the battery of the phone lasts more than 24 hours on a single charge. &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Redmi Note 9 Pro Max RAM and Processor&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;: You can buy Redmi Note 9 Pro Max in three storage options - 6GB of RAM + 64GB internal storage, 6GB of RAM + 128GB internal storage, and 8GB of RAM + 128GB internal storage. This lets you store all your files like songs, music, videos, games and more without worrying about space constraints. Also, you can easily switch between multiple apps with such high RAM capacity and expand the internal storage of the phone up to 512GB using a microSD card. In addition to this, the mobile is equipped with Octa-core (2x2.3 GHz Kryo 465 Gold &amp; 6x1.8 GHz Kryo 465 Silver) Qualcomm SM7125 Snapdragon 720G (8 nm) processor so that you can access multiple apps, play intense graphics games and browse the internet without any interruptions.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Redmi Note 9 Pro Max Connectivity &amp; Sensors&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;: Redmi Note 9 Pro Max comes with various connectivity options such as Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot, USB Type-C port, Bluetooth v5.0, Infrared (IR), 4G VoLTE, and a 3.5mm headphone jack. Sensors on the phone include ambient light sensor, fingerprint sensor, in-display fingerprint sensor, face unlock, proximity sensor, accelerometer, compass/magnetometer, and gyroscope.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h6&amp;gt;Xiaomi Redmi Note 9 Pro Max Price In India&amp;lt;/h6&amp;gt;Xiaomi Redmi Note 9 Pro Max smartphone price in India is Rs 16,999. Xiaomi Redmi Note 9 Pro Max was launched in the country on May 11, 2020 (Official). Thesmartphone comes in 2 other storage and RAM variants - Xiaomi-Redmi-Note-9-Pro-Max-128GB, Xiaomi-Redmi-Note-9-Pro-Max-8GB-RAM. As for the colour options, the Xiaomi Redmi Note