(608, 'Xiaomi Redmi Note 10', 'xiaomi-phones', 16999, 0, 'https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/resizemode-4,msid-75751069,imgsize-400,width-270/75751069.jpg', '&amp;lt;div id=&amp;quot;&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;lIZA8&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;height:auto&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;span&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Redmi Note 10 is the new champion in the Xiaomi family offering an amazing performance as it comes with striking features and decent specifications. The phone is sleek and lightweight measuring 160.46 mm x 74.5 mm x 8.3 mm (height x width x thickness) and weighs approximately 178.8 grams. You can buy the smartphone in Frost White, Shadow Black, and Aqua Green color options at a starting price of Rs 11,999.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;This mobile from Xiaomi comes with a 6.43 inches FHD+ SUPER AMOLED display with 83.5% screen-to-body ratio offering you an immersive experience while watching videos and playing games with vivid and crystal clear visuals. The resolution of the screen is 1080 x 2400 pixels and 20:9 is the aspect ratio. Moreover, the phone’s screen has Corning Gorilla Glass 3 protection from getting scratches. &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Speaking about the camera specifications, Redmi Note 10 features a quad camera setup on the rear for capturing stunning pictures videos. There is a 48 MP primary camera with f/1.8 aperture, an 8 MP ultra-wide angle camera with f/2.2 aperture, a 2 MP macro lens with f/2.4 aperture, and a 2 MP depth sensor with f/2.4 sensor. Features on the rear camera setup include time-lapse, pro mode, night mode, custom watermark, portrait, movie frame, auto flash, face detection, touch to focus, and more. While on the front, you get a 13 MP camera with f/2.5 aperture for making video calls and taking selfies.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Redmi Note 10 is equipped with Octa-core (2x2.2 GHz Kryo 460 Gold &amp; 6x1.7 GHz Kryo 460 Silver) Qualcomm SDM678 Snapdragon 678 (11 nm) processor that lets you enjoy a smooth and lag-free performance while accessing multiple apps, browsing the web, and playing intense graphics games, and doing other things. In addition to this, the smartphone is available in 3 storage variants - 4GB of RAM + 64GB of internal storage, 4GB of RAM + 128GB of internal storage, and 6GB of RAM + 128GB of internal storage. Owing to such amazing RAM and storage capacity, you can store your pictures, games, songs, videos, and other files without any space constraints.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;You need not worry about battery drainage in the middle of a call, playing a game, watching a video, listening to music, and doing other stuff as the Xiaomi Redmi Note 10 smartphone is powered by a 5000 mAh Li-Polymer battery with 33W Fast Charging support. In addition to this, Redmi Note 10 runs MIUI 12 based on Android 11 operating system offering you a clutter-free user interface.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;You get various connectivity on the Redmi Note 10 such as 3.5mm jack, Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot, Bluetooth 5.0, GPS with A-GPS, GLONASS, BDS, GALILEO, USB Type-C 2.0, and more. Sensors on the smartphone include ambient light sensor, proximity sensor, e-compass, accelerometer, gyroscope, and side-mounted fingerprint scanner.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h6&amp;gt;Xiaomi Redmi Note 10 Price In India&amp;lt;/h6&amp;gt;Xiaomi Redmi Note 10 smartphone price in India is likely to be Rs 16,999. Xiaomi Redmi Note 10 is rumoured to be launched in the country on July 23, 2020 (Unofficial).&amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;', '', '{\"key_specs_\":{\"0\":\"\",\"display\":\"6.57 inches\",\"front camera\":\"16 MP\",\"battery\":\"4520 mAh\",\"processor\":\"MediaTek MT6873V\",\"ram\":\"4 GB\",\"rear camera\":\"48 MP + 8 MP + 2 MP\"},\"special_features_\":{\"0\":\"\"