(610, 'Xiaomi Redmi 9', 'xiaomi-phones', 11790, 0, 'https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/resizemode-4,msid-72871169,imgsize-400,width-270/72871169.jpg', '&amp;lt;div id=&amp;quot;&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;lIZA8&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;height:auto&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;span&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Xiaomi Redmi 9 is a budget-friendly smartphone that is available at a starting price of Rs 8,799. This budget smartphone comes with a 6.53 inches HD+ Dot Drop display that has Corning Gorilla Glass 3 coating for protection. The resolution of the screen is 720x1600 pixels and 20:9 aspect ratio. Dimensions of the phone are 164.9 mm x 77.07 mm x 9 mm (height x width x thickness) and it weighs around 194 grams. Besides, you can buy the phone in different color options like Carbon Black, Sporty Orange, and Sky Blue color options.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Redmi 9 from Xiaomi is equipped with Octa-core (2x2.0 GHz Cortex-A75 &amp; 6x1.8 GHz Cortex-A55) Mediatek Helio G80 (12 nm) processor that lets you multitask and play intense graphics games on the phone without any interruptions. Besides, the smartphone is available in different storage variants - 4GB of RAM + 64GB of internal storage and 4GB of RAM + 128GB of internal storage. Hence, you can store your images, videos, games, songs and other files without any space issues. &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Speaking about the camera specifications of Redmi 9, the phone features a dual camera setup for clicking some nice pictures. There is a 13 MP primary camera with f/2.2 aperture and a 2 MP depth sensor with f/2.4 aperture. Features on the rear camera setup include AI portrait mode, HDR, Phase detection auto focus, AI portrait mode, and more. While on the front, the smartphone sports a 5 MP camera with f/2.2 aperture for clicking some stunning selfies and making video calls. &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Xiaomi Redmi 9 houses a 5000mAh non-removable battery that supports 10W Fast Charge. Hence, you can use the phone without any worries of battery drainage in the middle of a call, watching a video, listening to music, playing a game, and doing other things. In addition to this, the smartphone runs MIUI 11 based on the Android 10 operating system so that you can have a clutter-free user interface. &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Redmi 9 comes with various connectivity options such as Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot, 4G (supports Indian bands), 3G, 2G, 3.5mm jack, Bluetooth, GPS with A-GPS, GLONASS, BDS, NFC, USB Type-C 2.0, and more. Also, the mobile comes with various sensors that include a rear fingerprint sensor, distance sensor, vibration motor, ambient light sensor, and accelerometer.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h6&amp;gt;Xiaomi Redmi 9 Price In India&amp;lt;/h6&amp;gt;Xiaomi Redmi 9 smartphone price in India is likely to be Rs 11,790. Xiaomi Redmi 9 is speculated to be launched in the country on August 21, 2020 (Expected). As for the colour options, the Xiaomi Redmi 9 smartphone may come in Ocean Green, Sunset Purple, Carbon Gray colours.&amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;', '', '{\"key_specs_\":{\"0\":\"\",\"display\":\"6.53 inches\",\"front camera\":\"8 MP\",\"battery\":\"5020 mAh\",\"processor\":\"MediaTek Helio G80\",\"ram\":\"3 GB\",\"rear camera\":\"13 MP + 8 MP + 5 MP + 2 MP\"},\"special_features_\":{\"0\":\"\",\"fingerprint sensor position\":\"Rear\",\"other sensors\":\"Light sensor, Proximity sensor, Accelerometer, Compass\",\"fingerprint sensor\":\"Yes \"},\"general_\":{\"0\":\"\",\"quick charging\":\"Yes \",\"operating system\":\"Android v10 (Q)\",\"sim slots\":\"Dual SIM, GSM+GSM, Dual VoLTE\",\"model\":\"Redmi 9\",\"launch date\":\"August 21, 2020 (Expected)\",\"custom ui\":\"MIUI\",\"brand\":\"Xiaomi\",\"sim size\":\"SIM1: Nano SIM2: Nano\",\"network\":\"4G: Available (supports India