(618, 'Apple iPhone 11 Pro', 'apple-phones', 99900, 0, 'https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/resizemode-4,msid-71064804,imgsize-400,width-270/71064804.jpg', '&amp;lt;div id=&amp;quot;&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;lIZA8&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;height:auto&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;span&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt; Apple launched its iPhone 11 series earlier this month. This comprises of iPhone 11, iPhone 11 Pro and iPhone 11 Pro Max. While the iPhone 11 is the ‘most-affordable’ new iPhone, iPhone 11 Pro Max is the top-end variant of 2019 iPhones. The iPhone 11 Pro lies somewhere between these two, having the best of both. &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt; The iPhone 11 Pro comes with a starting price of Rs 99,900. There are three variants of iPhone 11 Pro - 64GB, 256GB and 512GB. The new iPhone comes in four colour options - Gold, Space Gray, Silver and Midnight Green.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt; On the specifications front, the iPhone 11 Pro features a 5.8-inch Super Retina OLED multi-touch display with 2436x1125 pixel resolution. The iPhone comes with IP68 rating making it splash, water and dust resistant. Apple claims that it can tolerate water with up to 4 meters up to 30 minutes. &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt; The phone comes powered by the latest A13 bionic chip with third-generation neural engine. On the camera front, the iPhone 11 Pro boasts of a triple rear camera. This comprises of an ultra-wide, wide and telephoto camera of 12MP each. The ultra-wide lens has an aperture of f/2.4 and 120-degree field of view. The wide lens offers f/1.8 aperture. The telephoto sensor, on the other hand has an aperture of f/2.0. For selfies, the device offers a 12MP TrueDepth camera with an aperture of f/2.2. &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt; The iPhone 11 Pro runs in iOS 13 operating system and offers various sensors like Face ID, barometer, three?axis gyro, accelerometer, pro