(759, 'Test Phone', 'one-plus-phones', 123890, 1, '/Public/asset/images/2022/077715c1d498e2b6db25f0179e.jpeg', '&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;This new entrant in the OnePlus family comes with a 6.43 inches Fluid AMOLED display that has a resolution of 1080 x 2400 pixels and an aspect ratio of 20:9 that will offer you an exceptional experience while watching videos or playing games on it. Furthermore, this dual-SIM phone is powered by a Li-Polymer 4500mAh non-removable battery with Warp Charge 30T Plus fast charging support. Hence, you will have to worry about charging your phone frequently or its battery drainage while you are in the middle of a call, playing a game or attending an online class. Also, the smartphone runs the OxygenOS based on the Android 11 operating system offering you a clutter free and user-friendly user interface.&lt;/p&gt;', 'This new entrant in the OnePlus family comes with a 6.43 inches Fluid AMOLED display that has a resolution of 1080 x 2400 pixels and an aspect ratio of 20:9 that will offer you an exceptional experience while watching videos or playing games on it. Furthermore, this dual-SIM phone is powered by a Li-Polymer 4500mAh non-removable battery with Warp Charge 30T Plus fast charging support. Hence, you will have to worry about charging your phone frequently or its battery drainage while you are in the middle of a call, playing a game or attending an online class. Also, the smartphone runs the OxygenOS based on the Android 11 operating system offering you a clutter free and user-friendly user interface.', '{\"key_specs\":{\"0\":\"Key Specs\",\"Battery\":\"5250\",\"Processor\":\"Snapdragon 285\",\"Ram\":\"18 GB\"}}', 1, 5, 'test-phone', 'off', '&quot;&quot;', '&quot;&quot;', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-06 06:42:06'),
